name: central cityapartement- wifi- nice neighbourhood
description: 39m² apartment with beautiful courtyard of the house. quiet and safe upcoming neighborhood-located in old jewish quater and popular area of Vienna. Surrounded by nice bars and restaurants, 15 min walkingdistance to the middle of citycenter, close to many sights . 300m  to subway U2 Taborstraße. Next to the karmelitermarket (with delicious places to eat) and the Augarten. free wifi. touristtax of 3,2% is included in the price.
neighborhood_overview: the Karmeliterviertel became very popular in the last years. It offers many new pubs and restaurants and is located next to Augarten (huge garden good for jogging), to the concert hall of Wiener Sängerknaben (muth), and has the Karmelitermarket, which is best to visit on Saturday morning to get biological products. In summer the best nightbars are at the donaukanal, which is 5 minutes away.
host_about:
I am open minded and like travelling myself. I have spent many months in Latinamerica and Asia, where I got  in touch with Indian philosophie and meditation...
Now I mostly work in the field of contemporary art and I do my best to offer you a nice apartment next to the citycenter...!

The highly appreciated by the Viennese Prater recreation areas and Danube Island with vast green spaces and mature trees invite to go walking, cycling and swimming, and with the subway in a few minutes away. Experience one of the most peaceful areas of Vienna in our bright and modern 52m², 2-room apartment. It is newly furnished and accommodates up to 4 guests.

The apartment has a valid short-term rental permit (reference number MA37/777373-2024-1), allowing you to enjoy your stay without any worries.

neighborhood_overview:
Nestled along the tranquil shores of the Old Danube, this charming neighbourhood offers a serene and picturesque escape for those seeking an unforgettable holiday in Vienna. The Old Danube (Alte Donau) neighbourhood combines the best of both worlds - peaceful natural beauty and easy access to the vibrant heart of the city.

Natural Oasis:
Your holiday home in Old Danube provides a unique opportunity to immerse yourself in the beauty of nature. The pristine Old Danube Lake, with its crystal-clear waters, is the perfect place to cool off on a hot summer's day. Enjoy leisurely swims, rent a paddleboat, or simply relax on the sandy shores. The surrounding parks and green spaces invite you to explore scenic walking and biking trails, offering a sense of tranquillity and rejuvenation rarely found in urban settings.

Shopping Paradise:
Vienna's largest shopping centre, "Donauzentrum" (250+ Shops), is conveniently a 10-minute walk (entrance area 4) from the apartm

name: cozy, quiet, artistic room in a lovely house
description:
It´s a super cozy, lovely room in the quiet, charming house where I live.
You can sleep with window open, listen to the birds singing, reading a book, seeing the sunrise at the "Roten Berg".

I love to live here, working on my projects, receiving lovely people from other cultures and sharing my passion about life.

With the metro you need 35min to get to the city center.
To the palace of Schönbrunn, the Klimtvilla, you can walk.
Traditional restaurants & cafe places are close by :)
host_about:
I´m an artist, freelancer, coach and consciousness trainer. 
I love living the life as pure as possible, growing my own veggies, writing, painting, reading books, sharing life stories, getting to know other cultures. 
I enjoy having deep talks, sharing dinner, sharing my favorite places of the city and welcome you as a brother or sister of this universe. 
See you :)
